DOC.brief_summary: The purpose of this study is to assess the effectiveness and safety of transcervical foley catheter as compared to dinoprostone vaginal insertion for preinduction cervical ripening and labor induction in term parous women with unfavorable cervix.
DOC.brief_title: Foley Catheter Versus Dinoprostone Vaginal Insert for Induction of Labor in Parous Women at Term: A Randomized Trial
DOC.criteria: singleton pregnancy parous women gestational age >=37.0 weeks Bishop score <=5 intact amniotic membrane absence of labor live fetus with vertex presentation no previous uterine surgical procedure major congenital anomaly
